Nursing is a health care profession focused on promoting, maintaining, and restoring health, preventing illness, and alleviating suffering. It involves holistic care of individuals, families, and communities, using a systematic approach known as the nursing process (assessment, planning, implementation, and evaluation). Nurses rely on science, clinical knowledge, and patient preferences to guide care, and they work as part of interprofessional teams to educate, advocate for patients, and coordinate care. Nursing is dynamic and continually adapts to changing treatments, technology, and social expectations, with a strong emphasis on culturally competent, patient-centered care.
